  "key_flows": [
    "1. Signal ingestion: SignalChannelReader.read() → List<SignalRecord> → SignalProcessor.processSignal() → SignalProcessor.executeSignal() → SignalAction.arrived(SignalPayload)",
    "2. Signal scheduling: SignalProcessor.start() → scheduleAtFixedRate(process(), pollInterval) → process() → executeWithSemaphore(read all channels)",
    "3. Kafka channel: KafkaConsumer.poll() → ConsumerRecord → processSignal(record) → SignalRecord(id, type, data, channelOffset)",
    "4. JMX signal channel: external JMX call → signal(id, type, data) → Queue<SignalRecord> → read() → SignalProcessor",
    "5. Notification dispatch: NotificationService.notify(Notification) → filter enabled channels → NotificationChannel.send(Notification)",
    "6. Connect notification: NotificationService.notify(Notification, Offsets) → ConnectChannel.send(Notification, Offsets) → SourceRecord → ChangeEventQueue (via BlockingConsumer)",
    "7. JMX notification: JmxNotificationChannel.send() → store in List<Notification> + NotificationBroadcasterSupport.sendNotification(JMX Notification)",
    "8. Action provision: SignalActionProvider.createActions(dispatcher, coordinator, config) → Map<String, SignalAction<P>> → SignalProcessor.signalActions"
  ],

  "important_notes": [
    "Both signal channels and notification channels are enabled/disabled via CommonConnectorConfig.getEnabledChannels() / getEnabledNotificationChannels()",
    "SignalProcessor uses a Semaphore to ensure single-threaded processing; Kafka consumer requires same-thread close",
    "SignalProcessor.processSourceSignal() only triggers SourceSignalChannel (filters by class type)",
    "Multi-partition support: if partitionOffsets.size() > 1, signal data-collections field is parsed to route to correct partition",
    "KafkaSignalChannel filters by connector name (record key must match connectorConfig.getLogicalName())",
    "JmxNotificationChannel extends javax.management.NotificationBroadcasterSupport enabling JMX listeners",
    "SinkNotificationChannel sends Kafka Connect SourceRecord to the ChangeEventQueue for downstream Kafka emission",
    "LogNotificationChannel is simplest: just logs via SLF4J",
    "StandardActionProvider is the built-in SPI implementation; custom providers can be added via SPI",
    "Notification.Builder follows fluent builder pattern; Notification is JSON-serializable via Jackson"
  ],

